                        <condition key="deficient">The Ms. is worn and shows traces of intensive use. &#xD;
&#xD;
The back board is damaged by insects.&#xD;
The original binding is for the most part destroyed. &#xD;
The original sewing is only occasionally visible (e.g., fols. 10r, 19r, 26r, 36r, 39r, 47r).&#xD;
The sewing has been crudely repaired with three different types of recent threads (e.g., close to the head: fols. 26r-50r; close to the tail: 9r-25r, 40r-50r). &#xD;
The leaves of the quires are held together with parchment strips. &#xD;
Some fols. are affected by humidity (e.g., fols. 15r-20r).&#xD;
&#xD;
Fol. 1 is of irregular shape.&#xD;
Fol. 4 is mutilated, the upper margin is cut off.&#xD;
Fol. 180 is mutilated, 2/3 is cut off.</condition>
